content:
If I'm not mistaken, values >= 10 are only used in test/validator #2.

Since those two-digit values don't appear to be really necessary to the problem, it *would* make solving marginally easier to just do away with them.

You are correct two-digit numbers are not heavily used in test cases. While drafting the test cases I was considering but not sure is single-digit enough for all varieties. Now having it done, it looks like I can limit it to below 10, to make parsing the value a little easier.
Thanks your suggestion. Will update it later today when I find a time to.
